{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778696248,"nonce":"nHRy7HHsruFOTxVK9a3Svi08Ark=","message":"**Cross-cutting correction: go-cue alignment in trial-averaged profile metrics (`06f7faf`).**\n\nThe forward-velocity / hold-drift profile metrics used in `3702f54` / `f47abb1` / `2bc95fd` (vel-within-RMSE, vel-RMSE-ratio, pos-RMSE-ratio) and the velocity / hold-drift figures across the same matrices were originally computed by averaging trial-mean profiles in *absolute trial time* before the trial-axis collapse. Because `centerout`'s target-on duration is randomised per trial, this smeared the go cue across ~150 ms and biased the resulting RMSE values.\n\nResolved by a new shared analysis primitive `rlrmp.analysis.trial_alignment.align_trials(profile, idx, pad=nan)` plus two aggregation helpers:\n- `replicate_mean_curves(aligned)` — per-replicate `nanmean` across go-aligned trials, used for inter-replicate variance metrics (within/across-cell RMSE).\n- `pooled_trial_mean_with_band(aligned, band=\"sd\"|\"sem\"|\"none\")` — pooled (replicate × trial) mean with SD/SEM band, used for velocity / hold-drift *plots* where the intent is inter-trial variability over the full population.\n\nCross-cutting impact on the affected analyses:\n- **3702f54** — winner unchanged; vel-RMSE values shifted up ~5–45 %.\n- **f47abb1** — cell ordering unchanged; vel-within-RMSE up ~5–30 %.\n- **2bc95fd** — two clear winners unchanged; one marginal winner-status flip (`gru__jerk_motor_pre` from 0.461 to 0.552).\n- **410d7ac** — not affected (Δv used per-trial after-go masking before `max`).\n- All scalar per-trial metrics (peak vel, hold drift, pre-go RMS, TTP, CV peak vel) are unchanged across all matrices — they already used per-trial go-cue indexing.\n\nSpec JSON transform names updated to reflect the alignment step (`align_trials_to_go_cue`, `replicate_nanmean_over_trials`, `pooled_trial_nanmean_with_sd_band`) so future readers of the figure specs see the correct pipeline.\n\nDownstream: `bf71d86` (go-cue stratification diagnostic) can build on `align_trials` directly.\n\nFixed by commits `53362d9` / `0e14755` / `c7a7883` / `35769d1` on `feature/go-cue-alignment-fix`.","files":null}]}